<p>Performance rating or special rating is a hypothetical rating that would=
 result from the games of a single event only. Some chess organizations<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-uschess2020_17-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-uschess2020-17"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
<sup class=3D"reference nowrap"><span title=3D"Page: p. 8">:=E2=80=8Ap. 8=
=E2=80=8A</span></sup> use the "algorithm of 400" to calculate performance =
rating. According to this algorithm, performance rating for an event is cal=
culated in the following way:
</p>
<ol><li>For each win, add your opponent's rating plus 400,</li>
<li>For each loss, add your opponent's rating minus 400,</li>
<li>And divide this sum by the number of played games.</li></ol>
<p>Example: 2 wins (opponents <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-st=
yle:italic;">w</span> &amp; <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-styl=
e:italic;">x</span>), 2 losses (opponents <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" styl=
e=3D"font-style:italic;">y</span> &amp; <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=
=3D"font-style:italic;">z</span>)<br>
</p>
