<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Rating_floors">Rating floor=
s</h4><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DElo_rating=
_system&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D9" title=3D"Edit section: Rating fl=
oors"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span><=
/span></div>
<p>The USCF maintains an absolute rating floor of 100 for all ratings. Thus=
, no member can have a rating below 100, no matter their performance at USC=
F-sanctioned events. However, players can have higher individual absolute r=
ating floors, calculated using the following formula:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e AF=3D\operatorname {min} \{100+4N_{W}+2N_{D}+N_{R},150\}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mi>F</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>min</mi>
        <mo>=E2=81=A1<!-- =E2=81=A1 --></mo>
        <mo fence=3D"false" stretchy=3D"false">{</mo>
        <mn>100</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>4</mn>
        <msub>
          <mi>N</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>W</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>2</mn>
        <msub>
          <mi>N</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>D</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>N</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>R</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mn>150</mn>
        <mo fence=3D"false" stretchy=3D"false">}</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle AF=3D\operato=
rname {min} \{100+4N_{W}+2N_{D}+N_{R},150\}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/a69df8b08b5a3a67627a44321780306b03a7450b" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
