This update can be performed after each game or each tournament, or after a=
ny suitable rating period. An example may help to clarify:</p><blockquote c=
lass=3D"templatequote"><p>Suppose player&nbsp;<span class=3D"texhtml mvar" =
style=3D"font-style:italic;">A</span> has a rating of 1613 and plays in a f=
ive-round tournament. They lose to a player rated 1609, draw with a player =
rated 1477, defeat a player rated 1388, defeat a player rated 1586, and los=
e to a player rated 1720. The player's actual score is <span class=3D"texht=
ml">(0 + 0.5 + 1 + 1 + 0) =3D 2.5</span>. The expected score, calculated ac=
cording to the formula above, was <span class=3D"texhtml">(0.51 + 0.69 + 0.=
79 + 0.54 + 0.35) =3D 2.88</span>.
</p><p>Therefore, the player's new rating is <span class=3D"texhtml">[1613 =
+ 32=C2=B7(2.5 =E2=88=92 2.88)] =3D 1601</span>, assuming that a <span clas=
s=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">K</span>-factor of 32 is us=
ed. Equivalently, each game the player can be said to have put an ante of <=
span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">K</span> times the=
ir expected score for the game into a pot, the opposing player does likewis=
e, and the winner collects the full pot of value <span class=3D"texhtml mva=
r" style=3D"font-style:italic;">K</span>; in the event of a draw, the playe=
rs <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glossary_of_poker_terms" title=
=3D"Glossary of poker terms">split the pot</a> and receive <span class=3D"m=
we-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inl=
ine mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://ww=
w.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyle \;{\tfrac {1}{2}}K\;}"=
>
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mspace width=3D"thickmathspace"></mspace>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
            <mfrac>
              <mn>1</mn>
              <mn>2</mn>
            </mfrac>
          </mstyle>
        </mrow>
        <mi>K</mi>
        <mspace width=3D"thickmathspace"></mspace>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \;{\tfrac {1}=
{2}}K\;}</annotation>
  </semantics>
