regression.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-35" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-35"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>34<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-:0_36-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-:0-36"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>35<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> If we assume that the ga=
me results are <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Binary_random_varia=
ble" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Binary random variable">binary</a>, tha=
t is, only a win or a loss can be observed, the problem can be addressed vi=
a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logistic_regression" title=3D"Lo=
