<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Practical_issues">Practical=
 issues</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-br=
acket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DElo_=
rating_system&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16" title=3D"Edit section: Pr=
actical issues"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>]</span></span></div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Game_activity_versus_protec=
ting_one's_rating"><span id=3D"Game_activity_versus_protecting_one.27s_rati=
ng"></span>Game activity versus protecting one's rating</h3><span class=3D"=
mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DElo_rating_system&amp;action=3D=
edit&amp;section=3D17" title=3D"Edit section: Game activity versus protecti=
ng one's rating"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket=
">]</span></span></div>
<p>In some cases the rating system can discourage game activity for players=
 who wish to protect their rating.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-38" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-38"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>37<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup> In order to discourage players from sitting on a high rating, =
a 2012 proposal by British Grandmaster <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/John_Nunn" title=3D"John Nunn">John Nunn</a> for choosing qualifiers t=
o the chess world championship included an activity bonus, to be combined w=
ith the rating.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-39" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-39"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>38<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Beyond=
 the chess world, concerns over players avoiding competitive play to protec=
t their ratings caused <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wizards_of_=
the_Coast" title=3D"Wizards of the Coast">Wizards of the Coast</a> to aband=
on the Elo system for <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magic:_th=
e_Gathering" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Magic: the Gathering">Magic: th=
e Gathering</a></i> tournaments in favour of a system of their own devising=
 called "Planeswalker Points".<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Planeswalkerpointsarticle=
_40-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rat=
ing_system#cite_note-Planeswalkerpointsarticle-40"><span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">[</span>39<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"ci=
te_ref-planeswalkerpointsarticle2_41-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-planeswalkerpointsart=
icle2-41"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>40<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Selective_pairing">Selectiv=
e pairing</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-=
bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DEl=
o_rating_system&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: =
Selective pairing"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brack=
et">]</span></span></div>
<table class=3D"box-Unreferenced_section plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-co=
ntent ambox-Unreferenced" role=3D"presentation"><tbody><tr><td class=3D"mbo=
x-image"><div class=3D"mbox-image-div"><span typeof=3D"mw:File"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Question_book-new.svg" class=3D"mw-file-=
description"><img alt=3D"icon" src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedi=
a/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/60px-Question_book-new.svg.png" decod=
ing=3D"async" width=3D"50" height=3D"39" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-fil=
e-width=3D"512" data-file-height=3D"399"></a></span></div></td><td class=3D=
"mbox-text"><div class=3D"mbox-text-span">This section <b>does not <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citing_sources" title=3D"Wikipe=
dia:Citing sources">cite</a> any <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W=
ikipedia:Verifiability" title=3D"Wikipedia:Verifiability">sources</a></b>.<=
span class=3D"hide-when-compact"> Please help <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Special:EditPage/Elo_rating_system" title=3D"Special:EditPage/E=
lo rating system">improve this section</a> by <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Help:Referencing_for_beginners" title=3D"Help:Referencing for b=
eginners">adding citations to reliable sources</a>. Unsourced material may =
be challenged and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifi=
ability#Burden_of_evidence" title=3D"Wikipedia:Verifiability">removed</a>.<=
/span>  <span class=3D"date-container"><i>(<span class=3D"date">January 201=
7</span>)</i></span><span class=3D"hide-when-compact"><i> (<small><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal" title=
=3D"Help:Maintenance template removal">Learn how and when to remove this me=
ssage</a></small>)</i></span></div></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>A more subtle issue is related to pairing. When players can choose their=
 own opponents, they can choose opponents with minimal risk of losing, and =
maximum reward for winning. Particular examples of players rated 2800+ choo=
sing opponents with minimal risk and maximum possibility of rating gain inc=
lude: choosing opponents that they know they can beat with a certain strate=
gy; choosing opponents that they think are overrated; or avoiding playing s=
trong players who are rated several hundred points below them, but may hold=
 chess titles such as IM or GM. In the category of choosing overrated oppon=
ents, new entrants to the rating system who have played fewer than 50 games=
 are in theory a convenient target as they may be overrated in their provis=
ional rating. The ICC compensates for this issue by assigning a lower K-fac=
tor to the established player if they do win against a new rating entrant. =
The K-factor is actually a function of the number of rated games played by =
the new entrant.
</p><p>Therefore, Elo ratings online still provide a useful mechanism for p=
roviding a rating based on the opponent's rating. Its overall credibility, =
however, needs to be seen in the context of at least the above two major is=
sues described=E2=80=94engine abuse, and selective pairing of opponents. Th=
e ICC has also recently<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template" style=3D"whit=
e-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Man=
ual_of_Style/Dates_and_numbers#Chronological_items" title=3D"Wikipedia:Manu=
al of Style/Dates and numbers"><span title=3D"The time period mentioned nea=
r this tag is ambiguous. (December 2024)">when?</span></a></i>]</sup> intro=
duced "auto-pairing" ratings which are based on random pairings, but with e=
ach win in a row ensuring a statistically much harder opponent who has also=
 won x games in a row. With potentially hundreds of players involved, this =
creates some of the challenges of a major large Swiss event which is being =
fiercely contested, with round winners meeting round winners. This approach=
 to pairing certainly maximizes the rating risk of the higher-rated partici=
pants, who may face very stiff opposition from players below 3000, for exam=
ple. This is a separate rating in itself, and is under "1-minute" and "5-mi=
nute" rating categories. Maximum ratings achieved over 2500 are exceptional=
ly rare.
</p>
