<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Athletic_sports">Athletic s=
ports</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DElo_ra=
ting_system&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D24" title=3D"Edit section: Athl=
etic sports"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]<=
/span></span></div>
<p>The Elo rating system is used in the chess portion of <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chess_boxing" title=3D"Chess boxing">chess boxing</a=
>. In order to be eligible for professional chess boxing, one must have an =
Elo rating of at least 1600, as well as competing in 50 or more matches of =
amateur boxing or martial arts. <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Co=
llege_football" title=3D"College football">American college football</a> us=
ed the Elo method as a portion of its <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Bowl_Championship_Series" title=3D"Bowl Championship Series">Bowl Champ=
ionship Series</a> rating systems from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/1998_NCAA_Division_I-A_football_season" title=3D"1998 NCAA Division I-=
A football season">1998</a> to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/201=
3_NCAA_Division_I_FBS_football_season" title=3D"2013 NCAA Division I FBS fo=
otball season">2013</a> after which the BCS was replaced by the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/College_Football_Playoff" title=3D"College Fo=
otball Playoff">College Football Playoff</a>. <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Jeff_Sagarin" title=3D"Jeff Sagarin">Jeff Sagarin</a> of <i><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/USA_Today" title=3D"USA Today">USA To=
day</a></i> publishes team rankings for most American sports, which include=
s Elo system ratings for college football. The use of rating systems was ef=
fectively scrapped with the creation of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/College_Football_Playoff" title=3D"College Football Playoff">Coll=
ege Football Playoff</a> in 2014.
</p><p>In other sports, individuals maintain rankings based on the Elo algo=
rithm. These are usually unofficial, not endorsed by the sport's governing =
body. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Football_Elo_Ratin=
gs" title=3D"World Football Elo Ratings">World Football Elo Ratings</a> is =
an example of the method applied to men's <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Association_football" title=3D"Association football">football</a>.<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-51" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-51"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>50<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> In 2006, Elo ratings w=
ere adapted for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Major_League_Baseb=
all" title=3D"Major League Baseball">Major League Baseball</a> teams by <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nate_Silver" title=3D"Nate Silver">Na=
te Silver</a>, then of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baseball_Pr=
ospectus" title=3D"Baseball Prospectus">Baseball Prospectus</a>.<sup id=3D"=
cite_ref-52" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/E=
lo_rating_system#cite_note-52"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>51<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Based on this adaptation, both a=
lso made Elo-based <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monte_Carlo_met=
hod" title=3D"Monte Carlo method">Monte Carlo</a> simulations of the odds o=
f whether teams will make the playoffs.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-53" class=3D"ref=
erence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_not=
e-53"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>52<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup> In 2014, Beyond the Box Score, an <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/SB_Nation" title=3D"SB Nation">SB Nation</a> site, introd=
uced an Elo ranking system for international baseball.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-5=
4" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_=
system#cite_note-54"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>53<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In tennis, the Elo-based Universal Tennis Rating (UTR) rates players=
 on a global scale, regardless of age, gender, or nationality. It is the of=
ficial rating system of major organizations such as the <a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intercollegiate_Tennis_Association" title=3D"Intercol=
legiate Tennis Association">Intercollegiate Tennis Association</a> and <a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_TeamTennis" title=3D"World TeamT=
ennis">World TeamTennis</a> and is frequently used in segments on the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tennis_Channel" title=3D"Tennis Channel=
">Tennis Channel</a>. The algorithm analyzes more than 8 million match resu=
lts from over 800,000 tennis players worldwide. On May 8, 2018, <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rafael_Nadal" title=3D"Rafael Nadal">Rafael N=
adal</a>=E2=80=94having won 46 consecutive sets in clay court matches=E2=80=
=94had a near-perfect clay UTR of 16.42.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-55" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_no=
te-55"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>54<span class=3D"cite-bracket">=
]</span></a></sup> In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pool_(cue_sp=
orts)" title=3D"Pool (cue sports)">pool</a>, an Elo-based system called Far=
go Rate is used to rank players in organized amateur and professional compe=
titions.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-56" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-56"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>55<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> One of the fe=
w Elo-based rankings endorsed by a sport's governing body is the <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIFA_Women%27s_World_Rankings" class=3D"mw-r=
edirect" title=3D"FIFA Women's World Rankings">FIFA Women's World Rankings<=
/a>, based on a simplified version of the Elo algorithm, which <a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIFA" title=3D"FIFA">FIFA</a> uses as its offi=
cial ranking system for national teams in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Women%27s_association_football" title=3D"Women's association footba=
ll">women's football</a>. From the first ranking list after the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2018_FIFA_World_Cup" title=3D"2018 FIFA World=
 Cup">2018 FIFA World Cup</a>, FIFA has also used Elo for their <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FIFA_Men%27s_World_Rankings" class=3D"mw-redi=
rect" title=3D"FIFA Men's World Rankings">FIFA Men's World Rankings</a>.<su=
p id=3D"cite_ref-57" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-57"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span=
>56<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 2015, Nate Silver, editor-in-chief of the statistical commentary =
website <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/FiveThirtyEight" title=3D"=
FiveThirtyEight">FiveThirtyEight</a>, and Reuben Fischer-Baum produced Elo =
ratings for every <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Basketb=
all_Association" title=3D"National Basketball Association">National Basketb=
all Association</a> team and season through the 2014 season.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-58" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_r=
ating_system#cite_note-58"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>57<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-59" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note=
-59"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>58<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup> In 2014, FiveThirtyEight created Elo-based ratings and win=
-projections for the American professional <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/National_Football_League" title=3D"National Football League">Natio=
nal Football League</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-60" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-60"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>59<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> The English <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Korfball" title=3D"=
Korfball">Korfball</a> Association rated teams based on Elo ratings, to det=
ermine handicaps for their cup competition for the 2011/12 season.
</p><p>An Elo-based ranking of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nat=
ional_Hockey_League" title=3D"National Hockey League">National Hockey Leagu=
e</a> players has been developed.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-61" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-61">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>60<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup> The hockey-Elo metric evaluates a player's overall two-way play=
: scoring AND defense in both even strength and power-play/penalty-kill sit=
uations. Rugbyleagueratings.com uses the Elo rating system to rank internat=
ional and club <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rugby_league" title=
=3D"Rugby league">rugby league</a> teams. Hemaratings.com was started in 20=
17 and uses a Glicko-2 algorithm to rank individual <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Historical_European_martial_arts" title=3D"Historical Eur=
opean martial arts">Historical European martial arts</a> fencers worldwide =
in different categories such as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lo=
ngsword" title=3D"Longsword">Longsword</a>,<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Rapier" title=3D"Rapier">Rapier</a>, historical <a href=3D"https:/=
/en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sabre" title=3D"Sabre">Sabre</a> and Sword &amp; <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buckler" title=3D"Buckler">Buckler</a=
>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-62" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-62"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>61<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Video_games_and_online_game=
s">Video games and online games</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
w/index.php?title=3DElo_rating_system&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D25" t=
itle=3D"Edit section: Video games and online games"><span>edit</span></a><s=
pan class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>Many video games use modified Elo systems in competitive gameplay. The <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplayer_online_battle_arena" ti=
tle=3D"Multiplayer online battle arena">MOBA</a> game <a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/League_of_Legends" title=3D"League of Legends">League o=
f Legends</a> used an Elo rating system prior to the second season of compe=
titive play.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-63" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-63"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>62<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esports" title=3D"Esports">Esports</a> =
game <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overwatch_(video_game)" ti=
tle=3D"Overwatch (video game)">Overwatch</a></i>, the basis of the unique <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Overwatch_League" title=3D"Overwatc=
h League">Overwatch League</a> professional <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Professional_sports_league_organization" title=3D"Professional sp=
orts league organization">sports organization</a>, uses a derivative of the=
 Elo system to rank competitive players with various adjustments made betwe=
en competitive seasons.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-64" class=3D"reference"><a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-64"><span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>63<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></su=
p> <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_of_Warcraft" title=3D"=
World of Warcraft">World of Warcraft</a></i> also previously used the <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glicko_rating_system" title=3D"Glicko r=
ating system">Glicko-2</a> system to team up and compare Arena players, but=
 now uses a system similar to Microsoft's <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/TrueSkill" title=3D"TrueSkill">TrueSkill</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-65=
" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_s=
ystem#cite_note-65"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>64<span class=3D"c=
ite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The game <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Puzzle_Pirates" title=3D"Puzzle Pirates">Puzzle Pirates</a></i> u=
ses the Elo rating system to determine the standings in the various puzzles=
. This system is also used in FIFA Mobile for the Division Rivals modes. An=
other recent game to start using the Elo rating system is <i><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AirMech" title=3D"AirMech">AirMech</a></i>, usin=
g Elo<sup id=3D"cite_ref-66" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-66"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>65<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> ratings for 1v1,=
 2v2, and 3v3 random/team matchmaking. <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/RuneScape" title=3D"RuneScape">RuneScape 3</a></i> used the Elo sys=
tem in the rerelease of the bounty hunter minigame in 2016.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-67" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_ra=
ting_system#cite_note-67"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>66<span clas=
s=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Mechwarrior_Online" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Mechwarrior Onlin=
e">Mechwarrior Online</a></i> instituted an Elo system for its new "Comp Qu=
eue" mode, effective with the Jun 20, 2017 patch.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-68" cl=
ass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_syste=
m#cite_note-68"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>67<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup> <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Age=
_of_Empires_II:_Definitive_Edition" title=3D"Age of Empires II: Definitive =
Edition">Age of Empires II DE</a></i> and  <i><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Age_of_Empires_III:_Definitive_Edition" title=3D"Age of Empires=
 III: Definitive Edition">Age of Empires III DE</a></i> are using the Elo s=
ystem for their Leaderboard and matchmaking, with new players starting at E=
lo 1000.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-69" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-69"><span class=3D"cite-brack=
et">[</span>68<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Competitive <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classic_Tetris" class=3D"mw-redirec=
t" title=3D"Classic Tetris">Classic Tetris</a> (<a href=3D"https://en.wikip=
edia.org/wiki/Tetris" title=3D"Tetris">Tetris</a> played on the <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nintendo_Entertainment_System" title=3D"Ninte=
ndo Entertainment System">Nintendo Entertainment System</a>) derives its ra=
tings using a combination of players' <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Personal_record" title=3D"Personal record"> personal best scores</a> an=
d a highly modified Elo system.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-70" class=3D"reference">=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-70"><s=
pan class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>69<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span><=
/a></sup>
</p><p>Few video games use the original Elo rating system. According to <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lichess" title=3D"Lichess">Lichess</a=
>, an online chess server, the Elo system is outdated, with <a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glicko_rating_system" title=3D"Glicko rating syst=
em">Glicko-2</a> now being used by many chess organizations.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-71" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_r=
ating_system#cite_note-71"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>70<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/PlayerUnknown%27s_Battlegrounds" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Player=
Unknown's Battlegrounds"><i>PlayerUnknown=E2=80=99s Battlegrounds</i></a> i=
s one of the few video games that utilizes the very first Elo system. In <i=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guild_Wars" title=3D"Guild Wars">=
Guild Wars</a></i>, Elo ratings are used to record guild rating gained and =
lost through guild-versus-guild battles. In 1998, an online gaming ladder c=
alled <i>Clanbase</i><sup id=3D"cite_ref-72" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-72"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>71<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>=
 was launched, which used the Elo scoring system to rank teams. The initial=
 K-value was 30, but was changed to 5 in January 2007, then changed to 15 i=
n July 2009.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-73" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-73"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>72<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The site =
later went offline in 2013.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-74" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-74"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>73<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup> A similar alternative site was launched in 2016 under the name <i>Scr=
imbase</i>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-75" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-75"><span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">[</span>74<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> which also=
 used the Elo scoring system for ranking teams. Since 2005, <i><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Tee_Golf" title=3D"Golden Tee Golf">Gol=
den Tee Live</a></i> has rated players based on the Elo system. New players=
 start at 2100, with top players rating over 3000.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-76" c=
lass=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_syst=
em#cite_note-76"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>75<span class=3D"cite=
-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Despite many video games using different syste=
ms for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Matchmaking_(video_games)" =
title=3D"Matchmaking (video games)">matchmaking</a>, it is common for playe=
rs of ranked video games to refer to all matchmaking ratings as <i>Elo</i>.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Other_usage">Other usage</h=
3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</=
span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DElo_rating_sys=
tem&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D26" title=3D"Edit section: Other usage"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
<p>The Elo rating system has been used in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Soft_biometrics" title=3D"Soft biometrics">soft biometrics</a>,<sup=
 id=3D"cite_ref-77" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-77"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
76<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> which concerns the identi=
fication of individuals using human descriptions. Comparative descriptions =
were utilized alongside the Elo rating system to provide robust and discrim=
inative 'relative measurements', permitting accurate identification. The El=
o rating system has been used in biology for assessing male dominance hiera=
rchies,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-78" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-78"><span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">[</span>77<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and in automat=
ion and computer vision for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fabric=
_inspection" title=3D"Fabric inspection">fabric inspection</a>.<sup id=3D"c=
ite_ref-79" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/El=
o_rating_system#cite_note-79"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>78<span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Moreover, <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Online_judge" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Online judge=
">online judge</a> sites are using the Elo rating system or its derivatives=
. For example, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Topcoder" title=3D"=
Topcoder">Topcoder</a> is using a modified version based on normal distribu=
tion,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-80" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-80"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>79<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> while <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Codeforces" title=3D"Codeforces">Codeforces<=
/a> is using another version based on logistic distribution.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-81" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_r=
ating_system#cite_note-81"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>80<span cla=
ss=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-82" class=3D"refe=
rence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note=
-82"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>81<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-83" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"http=
s://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-83"><span class=3D"ci=
te-bracket">[</span>82<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The Elo rating system has been noted in dating apps, such as in the =
matchmaking app <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tinder_(app)" titl=
e=3D"Tinder (app)">Tinder</a>, which uses a variant of the Elo rating syste=
m.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:4_84-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-:4-84"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>83<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The YouTube=
r <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marques_Brownlee" title=3D"Marqu=
es Brownlee">Marques Brownlee</a> and his team used the Elo rating system w=
hen they let people vote between digital photos taken with different <a hre=
f=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smartphone" title=3D"Smartphone">smartph=
one</a> models launched in 2022.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-85" class=3D"reference"=
><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-85"><=
span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>84<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup> The Elo rating system has been used in <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/College_and_university_rankings_in_the_United_States#Reveal=
ed_preference_rankings" title=3D"College and university rankings in the Uni=
ted States">U.S. revealed preference college rankings</a>, such as those by=
 the digital credential firm Parchment.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_86-0" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#c=
ite_note-:1-86"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>85<span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-87" class=3D"reference"><a h=
ref=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-87"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>86<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a><=
/sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-88" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-88"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>87<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The Elo rating s=
ystem has been adopted to evaluate AI models. In 2021, <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anthropic" title=3D"Anthropic">Anthropic</a> utilized =
the Elo system for ranking AI models in their research.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-=
89" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating=
_system#cite_note-89"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>88<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/LMArena" title=3D"LMArena">LMSYS leaderboard</a> briefly employed the E=
lo rating system to rank AI models<sup id=3D"cite_ref-90" class=3D"referenc=
e"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-90"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>89<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</spa=
n></a></sup> before transitioning to <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Bradley%E2%80%93Terry_model" title=3D"Bradley=E2=80=93Terry model">Bradl=
