<p>The Elo rating system was featured prominently in the 2010 film <i><a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Social_Network" title=3D"The Social=
 Network">The Social Network</a></i> during the algorithm scene where <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mark_Zuckerberg" title=3D"Mark Zuckerbe=
rg">Mark Zuckerberg</a> released <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/F=
acemash" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Facemash">Facemash</a>. In the scen=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eduardo_Saverin" title=3D"Eduard=
o Saverin">Eduardo Saverin</a> writes mathematical formulas for the Elo rat=
ing system on Zuckerberg's dormitory room window. Behind the scenes, the mo=
vie claims, the Elo system is employed to rank girls by their attractivenes=
s. The equations driving the algorithm are shown briefly, written on the wi=
ndow;<sup id=3D"cite_ref-92" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Elo_rating_system#cite_note-92"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>91<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> however, they ar=
e slightly incorrect.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" s=
tyle=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W=
ikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=
=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (April 2019)">citation=
 needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p>
